  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Afghan Governance and Alternative Livelihoods (SAGAL)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhance the capacity of Cluster Level Development Councils (CLDCs), District Development Assemblies (DDAs), District Governors (DGs), and target line ministries (Ministry of Agriculture, Irrigation and Livestock; Ministry of Rural Rehabilitation and Development; Ministry of Women&#x2019;s Affairs; Ministry of Counter Narcotics, and Ministry of Economy) 

Mercy Corps:
Services from DAIL to stakeholders to be facilitated through associations
&#x2022; Support DAIL to provide stakeholders will up to date and accurate regulation information
&#x2022; Research and Demonstration services targeting farmers and input suppliers
&#x2022; Support the market by providing customer feedback and dispute resolution between suppliers and customers
&#x2022; The areas for capacity building support are to be aligned with any existing self assessment conducted with DAIL and contribute to a coherent strategic plan

Objective 2: Strengthen Input Supply Systems at the provincial, district and village level

Mercy Corps: 
For market development it is essential to build sustainable service delivery of various beneficiary groups through strengthening associations or informal groups of like-minded members. Through these associations or groups, the members receive competitive advantages for production and selling of produce than if they operated solely as individuals.
The level of capacity of existing associations and those groups that aspire to formalise the arrangement of collective action is very low.  In order to provide value-add services to their membership, efforts are needed to:
a) Improve the institutional strength of the association 
b) Improve the services delivered to membership 
The support activities described under this section will concentrate on building the institutional strength of the associations to manage services to its membership.  An indicative list of activities to be undertaken is:

a) Maturity Assessment and Index for each association &#x2013; to tailor training and mentoring plan to develop each organisation and measure progress

Objective 3: Promote licit livelihood opportunities through support to selected value chains and improved planning, coordination and implementation of development projects at the sub-national governance level 

Mercy Corps:
&#x2022; To improve agriculture input business knowledge, skills and technical knowledge of agriculture input marketing entities at all levels in the marketing chain in Helmand.
&#x2022; Improve market knowledge on agriculture inputs.
&#x2022; To promote sustainable development in better quality inputs 
Training and mentoring activities to be delivered to members in collaboration with association leadership include:
1. Business growth training 
2. Basic cash and financial management
3. Technical knowledge &#x2013; Improved Seeds
4. Technical knowledge &#x2013; Integrated Pest Management
Working with farmers/producers associations 
The objectives of association strengthening are:
&#x2022; To promote the development of strong farmers&#x2019; representation in Helmand.
&#x2022; To support organising for improved buying and selling behaviour
&#x2022; To advance and protect the common business interest of affiliated farmers organizations locally, regionally and internationally

Indicative training and mentoring activities to be delivered to members in collaboration with association leadership include:
&#x2022; Farmer productivity training (land use, new techniques &amp;amp; packaging)
&#x2022; Basic Cash and financial management
&#x2022; Cross visits to other provinces to learn from model farmers
&#x2022; Other ( office management and administration)</narrative>
